Short and stocky carapace, egg-shaped in lateral view; LV strongly overlaps RV all
                  around the carapace; ADB longer than PDB at both valves; AB large with maximum of
                  curvature located around mid-H;

Samples GM1, GM4, Quarry section, Williams Ranch Member, Cutoff Formation, Roadian;
                 sample 4 (GM5), MKCS1 section, ‘McKittrick Canyon’ Member, Bell Canyon Formation,
                 Capitanian; Middle Permian, Guadalupe Mountains, West Texas , USA (this work).
